<p>ordinary, we are all itching to get up &amp; see for ourselves what really is happening, for our blood is getting fired up with the tales.<br/>Another "order" was that we were to pack all our "valises" at once &amp; be ready to move at a moments notice carrying only our water sheets &amp; overcoats &amp; a liberal supply of "iron rations", so round we had to go &amp; warn our platoons, &amp; for a wonder they never squealed.<br/>Went to bed after this &amp; about 2 o'clock we were pulled out again to unload the ammunition timbers[?] which had just got back we pulled the whole Coy. out for this &amp; they turned out fairly willingly considering the late hour, it did not take long &amp;soon we were in</p>
